feedback_history.subject: Hi PINGALWAD SANKALP, Intracranial aneurysms are bulges in the brain’s arteries that often go unnoticed—until they rupture. That moment can be life-threatening, and it happens far too often. In this RSNA challenge, hosted with ASNR, SNIS, and ESNR you’ll build ML models to detect and localize aneurysms across CTA, MRA, and MRI scans. You’ll work with expert-labeled data spanning 13 brain vessels, curated from 18 sites around the world. With variation in scanners, protocols, and anatomy, this competition will be a real-world test of your model’s ability to generalize. Total Prizes: $50,000 Entry Deadline: October 7, 2025 Learn More Your work could help transform patient care and save lives by advancing AI-assisted detection and diagnosis. Good luck, Ryan Holbrook Kaggle Data Scientist

Dear Learner, Thank you for your application to the Infosys Springboard Internship 6.0. Unfortunately, you have not been selected for the upcoming cohort as you have not completed all the prerequisite courses within the deadline outlined in the learning path. Completion will not be considered if you skip the course contents and take up assessment directly.   You can join the next internship cohort, look out for our communication regarding launch of the same.   Stay tuned for more programs and opportunities from Infosys Springboard and continue to learn new skills.   Got a query? Write to springboard-support@infosys.com Regards, Team Infosys Springboard
